[2026-03-18T17:45:30.530Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016vdYm1TbEAss5ffxEPFEGQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's what changed:\n\n**`packages/orchestrator/src/db/triggers.ts`** — Added `getEarliestNextTriggerTime()` that queries `MIN(next_trigger_at)` from enabled triggers.\n\n**`packages/orchestrator/src/db/index.ts`** — Exported the new function from the barrel.\n\n**`packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts`** — Replaced the fixed 5s `setInterval` with adaptive `setTimeout`-based scheduling:\n- After each tick, queries `MIN(next_trigger_at)` across all tenant DBs\n- Schedules the next `setTimeout` to fire at exactly that time\n- Clamped to min 100ms / max 60s\n- Returns a `TriggerSchedulerHandle` with `close()` and `nudge()` methods\n- `nudge()` cancels the pending timer and fires immediately (useful when triggers are created/updated)\n\n**`packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts`** — Updated shutdown to call `triggerScheduler.close()` instead of `clearInterval()`.\n\n**Impact**: Deployments with infrequent triggers (hourly/daily) drop from 720+ unnecessary DB queries/hour/tenant to near-zero during idle periods, while time-sensitive triggers fire with sub-100ms precision instead of up to 5s late."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":291,"cache_read_input_tokens":49192,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":291},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94edd138-b98e-445e-81f3-4541be0bd2e3","uuid":"e4b7c805-2c68-4283-b3b1-db622f9a00d4"}
